{"key":"processedPost-19746378","value":{"id":19746378,"first":19746214,"last":19746410,"when":1395792228,"utime":"03/26/14 03:03 AM","content":"The bottom line is if anyone says to never mist, consider them an idiot and ignore the bad advice.<br /><br />A major pinning trigger is loss of moisture from the substrate after full colonization.&nbsp; Your substrate is <i>supposed</i> to slightly dry out, and then you mist to replace that moisture.&nbsp; Never saturate your substrate and never allow it to fully dry out.&nbsp; Especially never seal up a substrate where it can't get rid of excess moisture and metabolic gasses.<br />RR","title":"Re: SGFC - Misting bulk tray necessary?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}